26 LC 112 4338
House Resolution 52EX
By: Representative Burns of the 159th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Ava Olivia Derbecker and Faris Vincent Derbecker; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the tragic loss of Ava Olivia Derbecker and Faris
4 Vincent Derbecker, beloved sister and brother whose kindness, joy, and loving spirits
5 enriched the lives of all who knew them; and
6 WHEREAS, Ava Olivia Derbecker was born on May 2, 2013, and Faris Vincent Derbecker
7 was born on December 14, 2016, and throughout their lives, they brought immeasurable
8 happiness to their family, friends, teammates, teachers, and community; and
9 WHEREAS, Ava was admired by her friends and family for her gracious nature,
10 compassionate heart, and fierce devotion to those she loved, and she possessed a rare ability
11 to uplift others through her encouragement, loyalty, and genuine care; and
12 WHEREAS, her passion for soccer exemplified the qualities that defined her character, for
13 she approached both competition and friendship with determination, support, and a sincere
14 commitment to those around her; and
H. R. 52EX
- 1 -

26 LC 112 4338
15 WHEREAS, Faris was blessed with a curious mind, a creative spirit, and a remarkable
16 enthusiasm for learning, and he inspired others through his intelligence, humor, imagination,
17 and eagerness to explore the world around him; and
18 WHEREAS, devoted to his family and protective of those closest to him, he brought
19 adventure, laughter, and treasured memories to all who shared in his journey; and
20 WHEREAS, together, Ava and Faris shared a special bond rooted in their love for family,
21 faith, and soccer, and whether at home, among friends, or on the field, they brought warmth,
22 encouragement, and happiness wherever they went; and
23 WHEREAS, Ava Olivia Derbecker and Faris Vincent Derbecker will long be remembered
24 for their love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who had the
25 great fortune of knowing them.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Ava Olivia Derbecker and
28 Faris Vincent Derbecker and express their deepest and most sincere regret at their passing.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
30 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
31 family of Ava Olivia Derbecker and Faris Vincent Derbecker.
